  "runtimeMin": 110,
  "format": "Days before the 95th Academy Awards, Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins predict all 23 categories, will-win and should-win, with producer Bobby Wagner along for a prop-bet warm-up: Oscar runtime over/unders, how many times the show will reference last year's slap, and whether Tom Cruise takes the front row. Everything Everywhere All at Once is the near-unanimous Best Picture call, with All Quiet on the Western Front named the dark horse. They split on two will-win picks, Best Actor (Fennessey takes Brendan Fraser, Dobbins Austin Butler) and Best Original Score (Babylon vs. All Quiet), and the should-win picks lean hard on Tár. Recorded before the ceremony.",
